<paragraph id="664936D5492DFFCBFF2969ACFC23258E" blockId="5.[151,1436,1520,1700]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
This is still a very poorly known species and differs from 
<taxonomicName id="A1F64D56492DFFCBFC8369ACFC1E2523" box="[829,990,1520,1545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vivianiaceae" genus="Balbisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis id="5482EAC7492DFFCBFC8369ACFC1E2523" box="[829,990,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
essentially in its shaggier pubescence and stiffly erect habit plus its well-developed short shoots (brachyblasts). 
<collectionCode id="00E7AE10492DFFCBFBA56A4AFBF0251A" box="[1051,1072,1558,1584]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
critical revision of herbarium specimens, and preferably field studies are required to clarify the affinities of this taxon. 
<taxonomicName id="A1F64D56492DFFCBFB1B6A61FA41257C" authorityName="Ricardi" authorityYear="1957" box="[1189,1409,1597,1622]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vivianiaceae" genus="Balbisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stitchkinii">
<emphasis id="5482EAC7492DFFCBFB1B6A61FA41257C" box="[1189,1409,1597,1622]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Balbisia stitchkinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically intermediate between 
<taxonomicName id="A1F64D56492DFFCBFDC16A38FC842557" authorityName="Steudel" authorityYear="1840" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." box="[639,836,1636,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Cruckshanksia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peduncularis">
<emphasis id="5482EAC7492DFFCBFDC16A38FC842557" box="[639,836,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. peduncularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A1F64D56492DFFCBFC3C6A38FBF92557" authorityName="Reiche" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Phil." box="[898,1081,1636,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vivianiaceae" genus="Balbisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microphylla">
<emphasis id="5482EAC7492DFFCBFC3C6A38FBF92557" box="[898,1081,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. microphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and may represent either an independent, closely allied lineage, or a natural hybrid between the two.
</paragraph>
